Email templates – local rules for this directory

Overview
- Use @react-email/components with Tailwind for all styling. No exported style objects. Avoid inline style props unless absolutely necessary for email client quirks (e.g., width/height on Img).
- Do not set a global/parent Body background color. Default to neutral/white backgrounds and a centered card container.
- Place <Preview> outside the Tailwind wrapper; keep sensible default props so templates render standalone (no separate preview version).
- Fonts: include Font for "Outfit" (weight ~600) and "Geist" (weight ~500) with an Arial fallback.
- Brand: expose a Tailwind color named brand = #7C3AED. Use it for CTA buttons/links.

Layout patterns
- Container: card-style wrapper
  - className: "mx-auto my-10 max-w-[600px] rounded border border-solid border-neutral-200 bg-white px-10 py-5"
  - Use Heading for titles (e.g., text-2xl font-semibold text-black).
- Avoid CSS grid/flex for multi-column content; prefer table-based structures or inline text for maximum email compatibility (especially Outlook).
- Stats/KPIs: prefer a single-line "statline" instead of a grid.
  - Wrap label/value pairs in: "inline-block whitespace-nowrap".
  - Use non‑breaking spaces between words in labels (e.g., 'TOTAL\u00A0SENT').
  - Separate items with middot separators "•" using a muted color: "mx-3 text-neutral-300".
  - Label style: "uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-500".
  - Value style: "ml-2 font-semibold text-neutral-900".
- If a multi-column layout is unavoidable, use a table with role="presentation" and simple borders. Do not use grid.

CTA
- Prefer Link styled as a button (anchor tags render better cross-client than button elements):
  - className: "rounded-lg bg-brand px-6 py-3 text-center text-[12px] font-semibold text-white no-underline".

Imagery
- Use INBOUND_WORDMARK for brand mark at ~32px height. Provide alt text. No Rounded corners.

Accessibility & typography
- Default copy in black/near-black for legibility (text-black / text-neutral-900). Secondary text neutrals only (e.g., text-neutral-600).
- Headings via <Heading>; body text via <Text>. Prefer text-base for body copy in transactional emails.

Tailwind wrapper config
- Tailwind component config extends:
  - colors.brand = "#7C3AED"
  - fontFamily.outfit = ['Outfit', 'Arial', 'sans-serif']
  - fontFamily.geist  = ['Geist', 'Arial', 'sans-serif']

